text: Tat Hims (), alternatively spelled Tathumus, is a village in northern Aleppo Governorate, northwestern Syria. About northeast of the city of Aleppo and just about south of Syria's border with Turkey, it is administratively part of Nahiya Akhtarin of Azaz District. Nearby localities include Qantarah to the south and al-Rai to the east. In the 2004 census, Tat Hims had a population of 1,722. ==References==
